<br>
For a long time now, people have been maintaining their jobs even though they don't deserve to because they charge more for labor than others do in another country.  However, the government passes unfair laws that prevent businesses from seeking out the cheapest labor.<br>
<br>
The government removes these protections and allows completely fair competition for business.  Now businesses can hire those people who will do the job for the best price.<br>
<br>
The people who have benefitted for some time now from laws that by which they were able to maintain jobs despite charging more for labor than others now deserve even more special treatment from the government?<br>
<br>
That's just absurd.<br>
<br>
NAFTA leveled the playing field.  There is no reason why we shouldn't have free trade.  If someone cannot compete, then he shouldn't get business.  We live in a capitalist country.  You have to be competitive to sell your goods or services.  That's the basis of capitalism, competition.<br>
<br>
By the way, we've seen a huge explosion in new jobs if you look at the country as a whole since NAFTA.  We experienced a huge financial boom after NAFTA went into effect.  I'm sure it wasn't all NAFTA, but there was no giant sucking sound as Perot expected there would be.<br>
<br>
The only companies that are going out of business are those that cannot or will not compete.  If the people in your town were willing to do the labor for the same price as those south of the border, they'd maintain the contracts.  The bottom line is they aren't.  If people in Mexico are willing to do the same job for less money, then they deserve to get that job.<br>
<br>
Ammelen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jebnar>Jebnar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 489<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/11/03 7:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=168.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another thing</span><hr size=1> the blue collar worker bends over and says &quot;oooooh, yeah! more daddy! MORE!&quot;<br>
